# Riverpod State Management Rules

Riverpod is the **single source of truth for all application state**.

State must be:
- predictable
- testable
- scoped correctly
- side-effect safe
- UI-decoupled

---

# 1. Allowed Provider Types

## Core Providers

| Type | Use Case |
|------|----------|
| `Provider` | computed / derived values |
| `StateProvider` | simple mutable primitives (UI atoms only) |
| `StateNotifierProvider` | legacy complex state (prefer NotifierProvider) |
| `NotifierProvider` | complex synchronous state with methods |
| `AsyncNotifierProvider` | async state with mutations |
| `FutureProvider` | one-shot async fetch |
| `StreamProvider` | continuous reactive streams |

---

## Rules

- [ ] prefer `NotifierProvider` / `AsyncNotifierProvider` over ad-hoc patterns
- [ ] **new** providers SHOULD use `@riverpod` codegen where possible (existing code may use manual `FutureProvider` / `NotifierProvider` until migrated)
- [ ] avoid manual provider boilerplate for new code unless codegen is blocked

---

# 2. State Ownership Rules

## MUST

- [ ] all state must live in Riverpod providers
- [ ] widgets MUST NOT own business state
- [ ] providers are the single source of truth

---

